		</p>
		<p>
			Since that moment, we have competed in the Roboboat competition 3 times, improving our boat more and more with each iteration. 
			What began as a rudimentary prototype has evolved into an increasingly sophisticated autonomous vessel, 
			with each competition providing invaluable lessons and opportunities for growth. Our team has expanded from 
			those initial founding members to a diverse group of over 60 students, all contributing their unique talents 
			to our shared mission of pushing the boundaries of marine autonomy.
		</p>
