		<h2>Our Structure: Many Minds, One Mission</h2>
		<p>
			The MHS Seals operates like a well-oiled machine, with four specialized departments working in 
			synchronized harmony. Each department brings unique skills to the table, and it's this interdisciplinary 
			approach that has become our greatest strength.
		</p>
		
		<h3>Computer Science Team: The Brain</h3>
		<p>
			Our Computer Science department brings our vessel to life with sophisticated algorithms that enable it 
			to "see," "think," and "decide." From intricate object detection systems that can identify buoys in 
			variable lighting conditions to navigation algorithms that plot optimal courses through obstacle-filled 
			waters, this team transforms our boat from a simple vessel into an intelligent marine system.
		</p>
		<Image image='/teams/computer-science.jpg' description='Computer Science Team' />
		
		<h3>Engineering Team: The Body</h3>
		<p>
			The Engineering department crafts the physical embodiment of our ideas. These innovative designers and 
			builders tackle challenges from hydrodynamics to structural integrity, creating vessels that are 
			both robust and agile. Their iterative prototyping process has led to breakthrough designs that have 
			significantly improved our competition performance year after year.
		</p>
		<Image image='/teams/engineering.jpg' description='Engineering Team' />
		
